{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"extinct-deranged-abalone","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Context\nPass 3 of the GitHub Code Quality remediation. Of 230 low-priority 'present' findings, 201 (import-style + config_schema table lambdas) are dismissed as churn/intentional. This ticket remediates the ~16 that genuinely improve reliability/maintainability, in a single change.\n\n## Scope\n### Tier 1 (real gains)\n- reconcile_helpers.py (AI-1): when no_sync=False, _env=None inherits the parent env, so a caller's REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off silently suppresses the live sync pull. Build an explicit env dict; only set REBAR_SYNC_PULL when no_sync=True; keep it absent/truthy on the live path. Add a regression test.\n- llm/fs_tools.py (#291): remove the misleading _SCAN_MAX_FILES constant (defined + documented but never enforced in search_files).\n- tests/unit/grounding (_HAVE_ASTGREP #310/#311): the capability flag is defined but never used in a skipif while siblings are — wire the guard where an ast-grep-dependent test needs it, or remove the dead flag if none does.\n- test_validation_depth.py (AI-3b): add non-review category coverage (e.g. category: transform) proving validation is category-agnostic.\n### Tier 2 (safe cleanup)\n- Remove genuinely-dead module-level constants/maps in src (reconcile_check reverse maps, resolve _REFUTE_ELIGIBLE_KINDS, acli_graph dead _RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK dup, _deprecations _KINDS, _engine_support/reads dead _SCRIPTS_DIR copy, engine_b candidate tuples — each verified unreferenced repo-wide before removal).\n- Remove dead test-fixture constants (unused _UUID_*/_ALIAS_*/_ENGINE_DIR/rubric; dead nested def _boom).\n- runners.py (#450): align the base/override run() signature (base requires agent_runner, override makes it optional).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] AI-1 fixed with a regression test that fails before / passes after and asserts the live path is unaffected by an ambient REBAR_SYNC_PULL=off.\n- [ ] _SCAN_MAX_FILES constant removed; no dangling reference.\n- [ ] _HAVE_ASTGREP either guards an ast-grep test or is removed; no unused capability flag remains.\n- [ ] AI-3b: a non-review category test case added and passing.\n- [ ] Each Tier-2 symbol verified unreferenced (grep) before deletion; behavior-preserving.\n- [ ] runners.py signatures aligned.\n- [ ] make lint + mypy clean; touched test modules pass; single Gerrit change lands only after LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1.","id":"62a3-a49d-04a0-4f18","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":["code-quality","codeql","cleanup"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Remediate Tier-1/2 GitHub Code Quality 'present' findings (Pass 3)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784431504420231001,"uuid":"74e72d3a-f2d6-4572-815b-3aee0d817dda"}